1
00:00:09,670 --> 00:00:16,100
♫ <i>The bicycle bell rings and takes me back to
the alley I saw in my dream</i> ♫

2
00:00:16,100 --> 00:00:20,240
♫ <i> I invite the sunlight to traverse the morning
fog and breeze with me</i> ♫

3
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:24,240
♫ <i>Riding my bike, trying to catch up to the fleeting youth</i> ♫

4
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:29,670
♫ <i>The Forbidden City made from red walls and
encaustic tiles in my memory</i> ♫

5
00:00:29,670 --> 00:00:33,770
♫ <i>Unlike the hustle and bustle of everyday life</i> ♫

6
00:00:33,770 --> 00:00:36,300
♫ <i>It's quaint and peaceful</i> ♫

7
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:41,620
♫ <i>Throughout the ordinary and extraordinary four seasons </i> ♫

8
00:00:41,620 --> 00:00:45,680
♫ <i>Some words are just like seeds</i> ♫

9
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:49,650
♫ <i>Growing in our youth, changing our future</i> ♫

10
00:00:49,650 --> 00:00:54,320
♫ <i>Who can understand the silence in our hearts?</i> ♫

11
00:00:56,110 --> 00:01:02,630
♫ <i>We once thought our dreams were somewhere far away</i> ♫

12
00:01:02,630 --> 00:01:05,800
♫ <i>We wanted to grow up as soon as possible</i> ♫

13
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:09,630
♫ <i>Some waited while some traveled</i> ♫

14
00:01:09,630 --> 00:01:12,350
♫ <i>How far away is our future?</i> ♫

15
00:01:12,350 --> 00:01:15,720
♫ <i>Now, each of us</i> ♫

16
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:18,690
♫ <i>Has gone through a lot</i> ♫

17
00:01:18,690 --> 00:01:21,800
♫ <i>We have grown up</i> ♫

18
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:25,650
♫ <i>Finally confirming that love is faith</i> ♫

19
00:01:25,650 --> 00:01:29,220
♫ <i>There's no need to wander anymore</i> ♫

20
00:01:29,220 --> 00:01:32,100
♫ <i>The questions we asked back then</i> ♫

21
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:34,780
♫ <i>Have been answered gradually</i> ♫

22
00:01:34,780 --> 00:01:36,640
♫ <i>Through the passing of time</i> ♫

23
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:40,120
♫ <i>Who had pursued their dreams and left no regrets behind?</i> ♫

24
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:42,400
♫ <i>Returning to this place in the end</i> ♫

25
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,060
♫ <i>Returning</i> ♫

26
00:01:44,060 --> 00:01:48,120
♫ <i>To the place that I've always loved </i> ♫

27
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:54,580
♫ <i>We once thought our dreams were somewhere far away</i> ♫

28
00:01:54,580 --> 00:01:57,750
♫ <i>We wanted to grow up as soon as possible</i> ♫

29
00:01:57,750 --> 00:02:01,600
♫ <i>Finally confirming that love is faith</i> ♫

30
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:04,660
♫ <i>There's no need to wander anymore</i> ♫

31
00:02:04,660 --> 00:02:06,770
<i>[Memory of Encaustic Tile]</i>

32
00:02:06,770 --> 00:02:09,770
<i>[Adapted from Beifeng Sanbaili's original novel "Memory of Encaustic Tile"]</i>

33
00:02:09,770 --> 00:02:12,270
<i>[Episode 18]
[The Person Who Stands in the Dim Light]</i>

34
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:20,593
What is it?

35
00:02:20,593 --> 00:02:22,810
I'll be leaving home tomorrow for the competition.

36
00:02:22,810 --> 00:02:26,800
Let me tag along when you visit Ms. Jin Ning in the evening later.

37
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:29,240
Ms. Jin Ning has been transferred to the intensive care unit.

38
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:31,630
They only allow four visiting hours per day.

39
00:02:31,630 --> 00:02:34,510
We can only see her through the window if we are to visit her in the evening.

40
00:02:34,510 --> 00:02:36,430
How long has it been like this?

41
00:02:36,430 --> 00:02:40,121
I met Sunian yesterday and had a long conversation with him. Yet, he told me nothing about it.

42
00:02:40,121 --> 00:02:44,570
Sunian never wants to talk about Ms. Jin Ning's sickness.

43
00:02:44,570 --> 00:02:47,140
Send him my greetings

44
00:02:47,140 --> 00:02:50,150
<i>[Beijing Qiming High School]</i>
if you happen to run into him.

45
00:02:50,150 --> 00:02:51,470
You should focus on the competition.

46
00:02:51,470 --> 00:02:54,640
You've spent a long time learning this, so you have to make us proud.

47
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:56,213
Don't worry.

48
00:02:56,213 --> 00:02:57,890
I'll get going, then.

49
00:02:58,300 --> 00:02:59,560
Hey!

50
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:04,120
What's wrong?

51
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:06,870
Aren't you going to give me a high five and cheer me on?

52
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:11,773
Break a leg.

53
00:03:11,773 --> 00:03:14,331
Don't push yourself too hard. Take good care of yourself.

54
00:03:14,331 --> 00:03:17,520
You should cheer up too, Ms. Jin Ning will be fine.

55
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:18,963
I've got to go.

56
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:22,150
Hey!

57
00:03:22,150 --> 00:03:24,360
Stop pulling a long face.

58
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:36,200
<i>[It takes 10 years of effort to sharpen a sword. Keep striving, seniors!]</i>

59
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:38,730
Are you all clear on that topic now?

60
00:03:38,730 --> 00:03:40,190
- Yes.
- Yes.

61
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:42,430
Those who didn't get it can meet me after class.

62
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:44,640
Okay. Class dismissed.

63
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:50,930
Sunian, wait.

64
00:03:50,930 --> 00:03:52,940
I need to talk to you. Meet me at the office.

65
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:55,300
Sir, I'm in a hurry.

66
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,630
Can we talk here?

67
00:03:56,630 --> 00:03:59,960
I know how sad you are, but you're a senior now.

68
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,840
You skip two classes a day.

69
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,240
If your mom ever finds out about this,

70
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,700
she won't be able to rest well and recover.

71
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:06,833
Sir,

72
00:04:06,833 --> 00:04:08,310
I've handed in all my homework. Right?

73
00:04:08,310 --> 00:04:11,730
- Yes, you have, but...
- I know what I'm doing.

74
00:04:11,730 --> 00:04:13,430
Thanks for your concern, sir.

75
00:04:14,670 --> 00:04:16,560
<i>[Class 3, Grade 12]</i>

76
00:04:20,630 --> 00:04:24,310
- Is he leaving early again?
- I thought he was a good boy and I didn't have to discipline him.

77
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:26,771
Only today, I've realized that I would never be able to discipline him.

78
00:04:26,771 --> 00:04:28,410
He's too assertive.

79
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:31,901
Forget it. None of us would feel motivated if we were in his shoes.

80
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:43,600
<i>[Intensive Care Unit]</i>

81
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:47,570
<i>[Waiting Area]</i>

82
00:04:51,430 --> 00:04:53,670
Is the visiting time over?

83
00:04:58,120 --> 00:05:02,253
Sunian, did you skip your classes again?

84
00:05:03,630 --> 00:05:05,970
You can't be doing this every day. If your mom finds out about this...

85
00:05:05,970 --> 00:05:09,940
Dad, I only want to see her.

86
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:16,620
I want to see her,

87
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:21,250
but not through the window.

88
00:05:21,250 --> 00:05:24,510
Let me talk to the doctor later.

89
00:05:24,510 --> 00:05:27,890
See if he is able to extend the visiting hours.

90
00:05:29,950 --> 00:05:32,370
Can he do that?

91
00:05:32,370 --> 00:05:34,230
Let me try talking to him.

92
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:02,610
Has Mom complained about anything today?

93
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:06,380
Of course, she has.

94
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:12,140
What did she complain about?

95
00:06:13,830 --> 00:06:15,530
She said,

96
00:06:16,950 --> 00:06:22,340
"There is nothing I can eat."

97
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:26,460
Your mom has a lot of cravings.

98
00:06:31,750 --> 00:06:33,483
Anything else?

99
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:38,230
There were a few times

100
00:06:38,230 --> 00:06:40,360
she woke up alone.

101
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:43,650
She was a little scared.

102
00:06:48,310 --> 00:06:49,940
Anything else?

103
00:06:51,270 --> 00:06:53,110
She said...

104
00:06:53,770 --> 00:06:56,170
that she missed us.

105
00:06:57,830 --> 00:07:01,350
Although we see her every day,

106
00:07:01,350 --> 00:07:06,780
she still feels like we spend a lot of time apart.

107
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,013
Dad.

108
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:30,410
Let's bring mom home.

109
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:41,090
It's better for her...

110
00:07:44,830 --> 00:07:46,770
to stay here.

111
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,920
It's your turn.

112
00:08:18,070 --> 00:08:20,090
35,800 yuan.

113
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:24,680
35,800 yuan.

114
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:28,630
Sorry. I didn't bring enough money.

115
00:08:28,630 --> 00:08:31,200
- I'll come back again.
- Sure.

116
00:08:32,450 --> 00:08:36,110
<i>[Payment Counter]</i>

117
00:08:42,870 --> 00:08:44,970
<i>[Liuli Hutong]</i>

118
00:08:48,390 --> 00:08:50,523
Shao.

119
00:08:50,523 --> 00:08:52,040
Zheng.

120
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:53,960
- Come in.
- Dongge.
- Come.

121
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,480
- Here.
- Did you just finish your dinner?

122
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:58,100
You haven't had yours yet, right? Let me cook you something. I'll be right back.

123
00:08:58,130 --> 00:09:00,790
I've taken my dinner. I ate something at the hospital.

124
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:03,610
Then... Take a seat.

125
00:09:07,460 --> 00:09:08,960
<i>Here's some water.</i>

126
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,733
<i>Zheng,</i>

127
00:09:12,733 --> 00:09:15,950
if there's anything you and Sunian would like to eat tomorrow, just let me know.

128
00:09:15,950 --> 00:09:19,210
I'll cook them for you. It won't take long.

129
00:09:19,210 --> 00:09:22,541
It's fine. It's very convenient to order takeout.

130
00:09:35,670 --> 00:09:38,880
Then... Jin Ning has been transferred

131
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:41,130
to the intensive care unit.

132
00:09:41,130 --> 00:09:46,850
<i>She has to always follow the doctor's orders.</i>

133
00:09:46,850 --> 00:09:49,120
Can she get used to that?

134
00:09:51,550 --> 00:09:55,000
She won't stop telling me

135
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,950
that she wants to get discharged.

136
00:09:57,950 --> 00:10:01,210
Can you talk to her when you're free?

137
00:10:01,210 --> 00:10:03,520
I'll try talking to her.

138
00:10:20,980 --> 00:10:24,320
Has it been busy at work recently?

139
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:26,870
<i>It's still the same at work.</i>

140
00:10:26,870 --> 00:10:28,403
<i>Don't worry.</i>

141
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:32,640
About that... Zheng...

142
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,390
You came at the right time.

143
00:10:34,390 --> 00:10:36,640
I need to pass you something.

144
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:41,440
This is a little something from all of us.

145
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:47,600
It's from the Restoration Division and the residents of the alley.

146
00:10:54,630 --> 00:10:57,200
Zheng, you must accept this.

147
00:10:57,200 --> 00:11:01,350
You're going to spend a lot on Jin Ning's medical bill.

148
00:11:05,170 --> 00:11:08,980
Then, I'll accept this.

149
00:11:08,980 --> 00:11:13,150
I might need to trouble both of you to list down

150
00:11:13,150 --> 00:11:15,120
how much everyone contributed.

151
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:17,670
In the future, I will return the money to them.

152
00:11:17,670 --> 00:11:21,570
You don't have to worry about that. We want to help you.

153
00:11:21,570 --> 00:11:24,910
I-I insist.

154
00:11:24,910 --> 00:11:28,070
Please, I beg the both of you.

155
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:30,713
Sure.

156
00:11:32,630 --> 00:11:34,630
I'll write the names down.

157
00:11:43,450 --> 00:11:45,240
You don't have to send me out.

158
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:47,730
My place is just right there.

159
00:11:47,730 --> 00:11:51,600
Zheng, let us know if you need any help.

160
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:53,320
We've been friends for many years.

161
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:56,120
There's nothing to be embarrassed about.

162
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:57,733
Sure.

163
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,460
I appreciate that.

164
00:12:19,910 --> 00:12:23,340
I guess Zheng was here

165
00:12:23,340 --> 00:12:25,800
to borrow money,

166
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:30,280
but he was too embarrassed to say it out loud.

167
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,900
I could tell.

168
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:35,720
It must be really hard for him.

169
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:47,270
Did you hear everything we said just now?

170
00:12:51,030 --> 00:12:53,800
You must not tell anyone about this,

171
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:57,830
especially Sunian.

172
00:13:01,790 --> 00:13:05,341
What's wrong? Why are you crying?

173
00:13:05,341 --> 00:13:10,810
I feel very sorry for Mr. Zheng.

174
00:13:10,810 --> 00:13:13,870
I feel sorry for Ms. Jin Ning

175
00:13:13,870 --> 00:13:17,590
and Sunian, too.

176
00:13:23,100 --> 00:13:26,780
It's okay. It's okay.

177
00:13:30,110 --> 00:13:33,390
<i>[Duty Roster]</i>

178
00:13:33,390 --> 00:13:35,840
Last but not least, let me conclude

179
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:39,120
<i>["Retreating Figure" by Zhu Ziqing]</i>
the theme of this article.

180
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:41,240
The author used simple language to describe

181
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:43,360
the love a father had for his child.

182
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:48,650
It's full of emotion, and is delicate, genuine, and moving.

183
00:13:48,650 --> 00:13:52,580
- From an everyday event, we were able to see a father's concern...
- Hurry up.

184
00:13:52,580 --> 00:13:54,640
- Why are you in such a hurry?
- and care for his child.

185
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:56,840
They have extended the visiting hours for Ms. Jin Ning.

186
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:58,390
I need to be there as soon as possible.

187
00:13:58,390 --> 00:14:01,330
All right. Class dismissed.

188
00:14:03,650 --> 00:14:06,670
I hope you're as keen on learning.

189
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,740
- Mr. Zheng.
- Xue.

190
00:14:39,740 --> 00:14:41,350
- Ms. Jin Ning.
- Xue.

191
00:14:41,350 --> 00:14:43,030
You're here to visit Ms. Jin Ning, right?

192
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:44,270
You came at the right time.

193
00:14:44,270 --> 00:14:46,670
You can have a chat with Ms. Jin Ning, I'm going to get some water.

194
00:14:46,670 --> 00:14:48,560
<i>[Quiet]</i>

195
00:14:56,450 --> 00:14:57,850
Ms. Jin Ning.

196
00:14:57,850 --> 00:15:02,960
Xue, it's been a long time since I last saw you.

197
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:04,600
I visited you a couple of times before,

198
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:06,870
but you were sleeping every time I was here.

199
00:15:06,870 --> 00:15:09,860
Sunian told me

200
00:15:09,860 --> 00:15:15,020
you were always running errands every time you were here.

201
00:15:15,020 --> 00:15:19,350
You were either fetching me medicine or buying takeouts,

202
00:15:19,350 --> 00:15:21,870
and were always occupied.

203
00:15:21,870 --> 00:15:23,670
Sunian is worn out.

204
00:15:23,670 --> 00:15:27,420
Since I have nothing else to do, I only try to help as much as I can.

205
00:15:27,420 --> 00:15:29,360
Yes.

206
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:31,950
They are worn out.

207
00:15:34,670 --> 00:15:37,970
We finally meet.

208
00:15:37,970 --> 00:15:42,150
There are many things

209
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:45,320
I want to give you.

210
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:47,560
Do you still remember

211
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:51,920
those boxes of mine?

212
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:54,900
Ms. Jin Ning, I want nothing from you.

213
00:15:54,900 --> 00:15:57,470
I only wish for your recovery.

214
00:15:57,470 --> 00:16:00,940
One day, I'll be gone forever.

215
00:16:00,940 --> 00:16:04,680
I'm sure you'll like what I'm going to give you,

216
00:16:04,680 --> 00:16:10,870
because... you're just like me.

217
00:16:10,870 --> 00:16:13,840
I'm reminded of my younger self

218
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:18,760
every time I see you.

219
00:16:20,935 --> 00:16:27,435
That's why I... like you the most.

220
00:16:27,435 --> 00:16:29,980
I like you the most too,

221
00:16:29,980 --> 00:16:32,220
so, Ms. Jin Ning, you must hang in there.

222
00:16:32,225 --> 00:16:36,595
You haven't taught me how to become someone like you.

223
00:16:36,595 --> 00:16:39,795
Don't be someone like me.

224
00:16:39,795 --> 00:16:44,585
You'll definitely be able to overtake me.

225
00:16:44,585 --> 00:16:46,725
Ms. Jin Ning,

226
00:16:46,725 --> 00:16:49,105
do you not want to talk to me anymore?

227
00:16:49,105 --> 00:16:53,995
Did you say this because you're sick of me already?

228
00:16:53,995 --> 00:16:57,265
I had a very smooth life...

229
00:16:59,225 --> 00:17:02,315
before this.

230
00:17:02,315 --> 00:17:08,365
I have Mr. Zheng, Sunian,

231
00:17:08,365 --> 00:17:11,235
and all of you by my side.

232
00:17:11,235 --> 00:17:14,985
God must be feeling jealous

233
00:17:14,985 --> 00:17:18,705
and wants me to return to Him as soon as possible.

234
00:17:18,705 --> 00:17:21,085
Ms. Jin Ning, you'll surely get better.

235
00:17:21,085 --> 00:17:22,805
You have to get better.

236
00:17:22,805 --> 00:17:29,185
Xue, can you do me a favor?

237
00:17:29,765 --> 00:17:32,625
I'm at your service.

238
00:17:32,625 --> 00:17:37,465
Take out the thing under my pillow.

239
00:17:44,335 --> 00:17:49,245
This is a voice recorder I prepared for Sunian.

240
00:17:49,245 --> 00:17:52,325
I told Sunian I missed you,

241
00:17:52,325 --> 00:17:56,555
and he gave me this.

242
00:17:58,055 --> 00:18:01,395
Make sure not to lose this.

243
00:18:01,395 --> 00:18:06,985
It carries things I want to say to Sunian.

244
00:18:09,615 --> 00:18:12,225
Ms. Jin Ning, whatever you want to tell Sunian,

245
00:18:12,225 --> 00:18:16,065
you can tell him in person.

246
00:18:16,065 --> 00:18:19,465
Every time I see you,

247
00:18:19,465 --> 00:18:23,675
it feels as if...

248
00:18:23,675 --> 00:18:26,635
joy has taken on human form.

249
00:18:26,635 --> 00:18:31,645
One day, when I'm gone,

250
00:18:31,645 --> 00:18:37,145
you have to share your joy with Sunian

251
00:18:37,145 --> 00:18:41,935
and help him get over this.

252
00:18:44,905 --> 00:18:47,575
Give me your words.

253
00:18:47,575 --> 00:18:49,745
Please?

254
00:19:01,465 --> 00:19:03,398
Ms. Jin Ning.

255
00:19:03,398 --> 00:19:04,575
Ms. Jin Ning.

256
00:19:04,575 --> 00:19:06,105
Ms. Jin Ning, what's wrong?

257
00:19:06,105 --> 00:19:08,375
Ms. Jin Ning, are you all right?

258
00:19:08,375 --> 00:19:10,715
Xue.

259
00:19:10,715 --> 00:19:15,705
Can you be my accomplice?

260
00:19:15,705 --> 00:19:17,465
I'm ready to help.

261
00:19:17,465 --> 00:19:23,505
I've been wanting to eat cake.

262
00:19:24,425 --> 00:19:27,555
Can you buy me a piece?

263
00:19:28,615 --> 00:19:31,765
Sure. I'll go buy you cake.

264
00:19:31,765 --> 00:19:34,435
I'll be right back.

265
00:19:34,435 --> 00:19:35,965
Sure.

266
00:19:51,505 --> 00:19:53,185
Madam, do you sell cake here?

267
00:19:53,185 --> 00:19:55,366
Sorry. We're out of cakes.

268
00:19:55,366 --> 00:19:57,058
Thanks.

269
00:20:02,135 --> 00:20:03,905
Madam, do you have cakes?

270
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,800
Sorry. We only sell bread.

271
00:20:05,816 --> 00:20:07,565
Thanks.

272
00:20:11,425 --> 00:20:13,636
Sir. Sir, I want to buy a cake.

273
00:20:13,636 --> 00:20:15,375
The baker has gotten off work.

274
00:20:15,375 --> 00:20:17,095
Is there something else you want?

275
00:20:17,095 --> 00:20:18,575
I only need a cake.

276
00:20:18,575 --> 00:20:20,775
I don't mind the flavors and the pattern.

277
00:20:20,775 --> 00:20:25,735
It's a matter of great importance for me, I'm begging you.

278
00:20:26,745 --> 00:20:28,405
All right. Give me a moment.

279
00:20:28,405 --> 00:20:30,238
Thanks.

280
00:20:58,550 --> 00:21:03,295
<i>[Peking Union Medical College Hospital]</i>

281
00:21:03,295 --> 00:21:07,345
Zheng, eat it while it's still warm.

282
00:21:07,345 --> 00:21:09,275
Dongge made this.

283
00:21:16,615 --> 00:21:18,305
Xue.

284
00:21:19,505 --> 00:21:21,455
It's past visiting hours.

285
00:21:25,985 --> 00:21:29,095
Did you buy this cake for Ms. Jin Ning?

286
00:21:30,525 --> 00:21:32,785
What's wrong with her?

287
00:21:32,785 --> 00:21:36,635
How could she make a kid buy her food?

288
00:21:36,635 --> 00:21:37,945
Don't worry about it.

289
00:21:37,945 --> 00:21:39,725
Xue, give it to me.

290
00:21:40,775 --> 00:21:48,265
Xue has received so many cakes from Ms. Jin Ning since she was a kid.

291
00:21:48,265 --> 00:21:51,575
Tell Jin Ning to live a long and healthy life.

292
00:21:51,575 --> 00:21:54,545
Xue has to pay her back.

293
00:21:55,855 --> 00:22:01,055
Do you think Ms. Jin Ning is still able to eat the cake?

294
00:22:05,805 --> 00:22:08,405
I'll show her the cake.

295
00:22:15,565 --> 00:22:19,375
I should have gotten here sooner.

296
00:22:19,375 --> 00:22:21,615
Don't beat yourself up.

297
00:22:21,615 --> 00:22:24,925
Ms. Jin Ning is just making a fuss.

298
00:22:24,925 --> 00:22:28,655
In fact, she has completely lost her appetite.

299
00:22:31,575 --> 00:22:34,908
Xue. Xue.

300
00:22:37,135 --> 00:22:40,505
You should go home now lest your mom worries about you.

301
00:22:40,505 --> 00:22:43,365
I'll stay here tonight to keep Mr. Zheng company.

302
00:22:43,365 --> 00:22:45,715
It's okay, Shao Hua.

303
00:22:45,715 --> 00:22:48,615
Go home with Xue. It's late now.

304
00:22:48,615 --> 00:22:50,366
- It's not safe for her to go home on her own.
- You don't have to worry about that.

305
00:22:50,366 --> 00:22:51,615
I've already informed Dongge about this.

306
00:22:51,615 --> 00:22:53,055
- No, but...
- She won't worry about me.

307
00:22:53,055 --> 00:22:55,885
- You don't have to do that...
- It's fine. We're all worried about you.

308
00:22:55,885 --> 00:22:58,405
I'm begging you.

309
00:23:01,775 --> 00:23:06,605
I simply want to stay with her alone.

310
00:23:16,425 --> 00:23:20,095
But... Zheng.

311
00:23:22,745 --> 00:23:26,025
You're now the only responsible adult in the household.

312
00:23:26,025 --> 00:23:29,525
You need to eat more, don't fall sick.

313
00:23:32,025 --> 00:23:33,645
I won't.

314
00:23:38,275 --> 00:23:40,125
Fine. I'll get going.

315
00:23:41,375 --> 00:23:43,540
Thanks, Xue.

316
00:23:44,485 --> 00:23:46,615
Bye, Mr. Zheng.

317
00:23:46,615 --> 00:23:48,148
Bye.

318
00:23:48,148 --> 00:23:49,935
Let's go.

319
00:23:57,425 --> 00:24:03,075
Zheng, just let me know if you need any help.

320
00:24:03,075 --> 00:24:05,075
We're all here for you.

321
00:24:07,775 --> 00:24:09,275
We'll get going now.

322
00:24:50,270 --> 00:24:52,950
<i>[Peking Union Medical College Hospital]</i>

323
00:24:53,805 --> 00:24:59,025
Dad, I will go and buy another cake for Ms. Jin Ning tomorrow.

324
00:24:59,025 --> 00:25:02,825
Sure. I'll come along.

325
00:25:03,655 --> 00:25:05,388
Don't worry.

326
00:25:05,388 --> 00:25:08,965
Sunian. Sunian!

327
00:25:14,705 --> 00:25:16,545
Mr. Shao.

328
00:25:17,745 --> 00:25:19,945
Sunian, did you just come from school?

329
00:25:22,135 --> 00:25:24,885
It's past the visiting hours.

330
00:25:26,845 --> 00:25:28,578
I know.

331
00:25:31,305 --> 00:25:36,205
I just want to see my mom again.

332
00:25:40,515 --> 00:25:42,265
Go ahead.

333
00:26:43,010 --> 00:26:47,930
<i>Emergency Resuscitation]</i>

334
00:26:57,900 --> 00:27:00,250
<i>[Waiting area]</i>

335
00:27:04,715 --> 00:27:06,348
Ning,

336
00:27:07,645 --> 00:27:09,885
I'm right here.

337
00:27:11,955 --> 00:27:14,305
Sunian is here, too.

338
00:27:22,845 --> 00:27:25,105
Why do you...

339
00:27:25,105 --> 00:27:29,805
look more ill than me?

340
00:27:31,035 --> 00:27:33,135
That's not true.

341
00:27:33,135 --> 00:27:35,405
We're doing very well.

342
00:27:37,055 --> 00:27:41,925
Sunian, from now on,

343
00:27:41,925 --> 00:27:46,455
I will become a star

344
00:27:46,455 --> 00:27:49,070
in the dark sky.

345
00:27:49,535 --> 00:27:54,685
I'll be happy when you achieve something.

346
00:27:55,755 --> 00:28:01,375
I'll laugh at you when you make a mistake.

347
00:28:02,745 --> 00:28:08,595
Just look up into the sky when you miss me.

348
00:28:10,645 --> 00:28:12,445
Initially,

349
00:28:12,445 --> 00:28:16,415
I wanted to take a look...

350
00:28:17,705 --> 00:28:20,835
at your smiling face,

351
00:28:21,815 --> 00:28:23,348
but I think...

352
00:28:24,475 --> 00:28:27,065
that will be too hard for you.

353
00:28:31,305 --> 00:28:33,585
Good boy.

354
00:28:47,025 --> 00:28:49,385
Zheng.

355
00:28:49,385 --> 00:28:52,475
I'm right here. I'll always be here.

356
00:28:53,605 --> 00:28:58,145
You are good at everything,

357
00:28:58,985 --> 00:29:01,985
except that you're an introvert.

358
00:29:04,515 --> 00:29:06,805
Back then,

359
00:29:06,805 --> 00:29:10,225
I was always the one

360
00:29:10,225 --> 00:29:13,165
who socialized with others.

361
00:29:13,885 --> 00:29:16,035
From now on,

362
00:29:16,955 --> 00:29:20,195
you have to do it yourself.

363
00:29:20,195 --> 00:29:22,475
I'll do it.

364
00:29:22,475 --> 00:29:25,125
I can do everything by myself,

365
00:29:25,825 --> 00:29:29,785
but I want you by my...

366
00:29:29,785 --> 00:29:33,245
I can only get those things done with you by my side.

367
00:29:37,515 --> 00:29:40,005
Zheng Jin.

368
00:29:42,715 --> 00:29:44,865
I don't want...

369
00:29:46,165 --> 00:29:49,335
to leave you.

370
00:29:51,335 --> 00:29:53,705
Remember to come and meet me...

371
00:29:56,035 --> 00:29:59,105
in your next life.

372
00:30:01,195 --> 00:30:03,305
In our next lives...

373
00:30:03,305 --> 00:30:07,095
We'll surely be with each other again in our next lives.

374
00:30:07,095 --> 00:30:10,565
We'll still be working at the Restoration Department.

375
00:30:10,565 --> 00:30:16,725
You'll still ride a bike and bring me everywhere you go.

376
00:30:16,725 --> 00:30:21,565
You will... You will buy me a new music box.

377
00:30:21,565 --> 00:30:25,685
I know how to fix it. I'll fix it for you.

378
00:30:39,235 --> 00:30:41,335
Doesn't it sound nice?

379
00:31:14,125 --> 00:31:15,750
Ning'er.

380
00:31:16,385 --> 00:31:18,325
Ning'er.

381
00:31:29,845 --> 00:31:33,926
Ning'er, open your eyes. The song is still playing.

382
00:31:36,265 --> 00:31:38,855
Ning'er!

383
00:31:39,705 --> 00:31:43,545
Ning'er, I can't live without you.

384
00:31:43,545 --> 00:31:45,635
Ning'er!

385
00:31:46,500 --> 00:31:50,760
♫ <i>Carved into the days long gone</i> ♫

386
00:31:50,760 --> 00:31:53,510
♫ <i>Although simplicity is plain...</i> ♫

387
00:31:54,110 --> 00:31:57,405
Ning'er!

388
00:31:57,405 --> 00:32:00,445
Jin Ning!

389
00:32:01,465 --> 00:32:03,535
Ning'er!

390
00:32:08,475 --> 00:32:12,875
Ning'er, I can't live without you!

391
00:32:13,925 --> 00:32:16,765
Ning'er, wake up!

392
00:32:16,765 --> 00:32:20,220
I can't live without you.

393
00:32:21,885 --> 00:32:25,565
Ning'er!

394
00:32:25,565 --> 00:32:29,755
I can't live without you!

395
00:32:34,440 --> 00:32:37,730
<i>[Liuli Hutong]</i>

396
00:32:39,945 --> 00:32:42,095
This alley looks quite unique.

397
00:32:42,095 --> 00:32:44,185
Yes. Liuli Hutong has been here for some time.

398
00:32:44,185 --> 00:32:45,555
Yeah. This place is quite beautiful.

399
00:32:45,555 --> 00:32:47,488
Yes.

400
00:32:48,485 --> 00:32:51,685
<i>[Funeral]</i>
- It's quite a beautiful place.
- Someone in this household passed away.

401
00:32:51,685 --> 00:32:53,455
That brings bad luck. Sir, can you please hurry?

402
00:32:53,455 --> 00:32:55,175
- Please hurry.
- Sure.

403
00:33:06,805 --> 00:33:09,275
<i>She had stayed in the same hutong for many years.</i>

404
00:33:09,275 --> 00:33:12,355
I can't believe this has happened.

405
00:33:12,355 --> 00:33:15,955
Jin Ning was such a kind person.

406
00:33:15,955 --> 00:33:18,835
It's a pity that she died an untimely death.

407
00:33:18,835 --> 00:33:20,895
Yes, leaving her husband and son behind.

408
00:33:20,895 --> 00:33:22,835
What are they going to do in the future?

409
00:33:22,835 --> 00:33:26,485
The father and the son will have a tough time ahead.

410
00:33:30,710 --> 00:33:35,720
<i>[Tears of remembrance]</i>

411
00:33:51,795 --> 00:33:53,935
Jin Ning.

412
00:33:55,185 --> 00:33:58,565
If reincarnation is real,

413
00:33:59,215 --> 00:34:01,715
I'd like to take you as my apprentice again.

414
00:34:17,310 --> 00:34:22,450
<i>[In Remembrance of Ms. Jin Ning]</i>

415
00:34:52,285 --> 00:34:54,185
Xue.

416
00:34:54,185 --> 00:34:56,735
Have you bought everything I told you to buy?

417
00:34:56,735 --> 00:34:58,335
They are right here.

418
00:34:59,065 --> 00:35:02,805
Mom, where is Sunian?

419
00:35:02,805 --> 00:35:07,795
He has locked himself up in his room for days.

420
00:35:07,795 --> 00:35:09,905
You should go talk to him.

421
00:35:51,685 --> 00:35:54,135
Sunian.

422
00:35:59,275 --> 00:36:02,255
You shouldn't stay here alone.

423
00:36:02,255 --> 00:36:06,425
Why don't we go take a stroll outside?

424
00:36:15,435 --> 00:36:18,965
Sunian, is there anything you want to eat?

425
00:36:18,965 --> 00:36:21,735
Let me get them for you.

426
00:36:28,935 --> 00:36:31,215
Sunian,

427
00:36:32,155 --> 00:36:36,775
don't hold back if you feel like crying.

428
00:36:36,775 --> 00:36:39,365
Don't keep it all to yourself.

429
00:36:55,385 --> 00:36:58,885
Before Ms. Jin Ning passed away,

430
00:36:58,885 --> 00:37:01,315
she recorded a message for you

431
00:37:01,315 --> 00:37:03,885
in this voice recorder.

432
00:37:16,025 --> 00:37:18,285
You should check it out.

433
00:37:19,425 --> 00:37:21,775
I'll leave you alone for now.

434
00:37:21,775 --> 00:37:24,485
Just call my name when you need me.

435
00:37:24,485 --> 00:37:27,525
I'll be right at your door. I'm not going anywhere else.

436
00:38:08,935 --> 00:38:10,420
<i>Hey.</i>

437
00:38:11,275 --> 00:38:13,255
<i>Hey.</i>

438
00:38:13,255 --> 00:38:15,705
<i>Sunian.</i>

439
00:38:16,635 --> 00:38:21,265
<i>I'm leaving.</i>

440
00:38:21,265 --> 00:38:25,385
<i>Please don't hate me.</i>

441
00:38:26,375 --> 00:38:31,505
<i>I'm very blessed to have you as my son.</i>

442
00:38:32,415 --> 00:38:35,915
<i>I heard people complimenting you</i>

443
00:38:35,915 --> 00:38:38,895
<i>every time I attended a parent's meeting.</i>

444
00:38:38,895 --> 00:38:43,985
<i>They wanted to know how I raised you.</i>

445
00:38:45,815 --> 00:38:50,805
<i>I could only reply with some silly answers.</i>

446
00:38:50,805 --> 00:38:52,515
<i>When I came home,</i>

447
00:38:52,515 --> 00:38:55,505
<i>I acted out the scenario in front of your dad</i>

448
00:38:55,505 --> 00:38:57,985
<i>to cheer him up.</i>

449
00:39:01,335 --> 00:39:04,285
<i>Thinking back,</i>

450
00:39:04,285 --> 00:39:09,535
<i>I think I've never really had to discipline you.</i>

451
00:39:10,275 --> 00:39:13,705
<i>You've always been a good boy.</i>

452
00:39:13,705 --> 00:39:18,745
<i>Sometimes, I got upset with you</i>

453
00:39:18,745 --> 00:39:22,585
<i>because you never acted like a kid.</i>

454
00:39:22,585 --> 00:39:26,775
<i>You never fussed, whined,</i>

455
00:39:26,775 --> 00:39:28,855
<i>or acted cute in front of me.</i>

456
00:39:29,855 --> 00:39:31,940
<i>In fact,</i>

457
00:39:32,375 --> 00:39:35,430
<i>I was worried</i>

458
00:39:36,045 --> 00:39:38,845
<i>that we wouldn't share a close relationship.</i>

459
00:39:39,685 --> 00:39:42,875
<i>Since you entered your teen years,</i>

460
00:39:42,875 --> 00:39:46,845
<i>you'd never hugged me</i>

461
00:39:46,845 --> 00:39:49,205
<i>and said to me,</i>

462
00:39:49,205 --> 00:39:52,400
<i>"Mom, I like you so much."</i>

463
00:39:52,865 --> 00:39:57,385
<i>And now, that will certainly not happen again.</i>

464
00:39:57,385 --> 00:40:00,395
<i>I'm so ugly right now.</i>

465
00:40:00,395 --> 00:40:02,585
<i>I look terrifying.</i>

466
00:40:02,585 --> 00:40:05,555
<i>You don't even dare come near me,</i>

467
00:40:06,315 --> 00:40:10,275
<i>much less hug me.</i>

468
00:40:10,275 --> 00:40:14,035
<i>Since I was transferred to the intensive care unit,</i>

469
00:40:14,755 --> 00:40:19,265
<i>you must have thought that I was always asleep.</i>

470
00:40:20,235 --> 00:40:22,285
<i>In fact,</i>

471
00:40:22,905 --> 00:40:26,165
<i>I was always taking a peek at both of you</i>

472
00:40:26,165 --> 00:40:29,365
<i>when I was awake.</i>

473
00:40:30,355 --> 00:40:33,535
<i>I saw your dad,</i>

474
00:40:33,535 --> 00:40:38,615
<i>trying to hold back his tears.</i>

475
00:40:40,155 --> 00:40:42,485
<i>I saw you,</i>

476
00:40:43,175 --> 00:40:48,155
<i>staring at me timidly.</i>

477
00:40:48,155 --> 00:40:52,355
<i>You're afraid of me, right?</i>

478
00:41:00,905 --> 00:41:05,905
<i>That's why you must not remember</i>

479
00:41:05,905 --> 00:41:09,205
<i>how I look during this period.</i>

480
00:41:09,205 --> 00:41:14,935
<i>You should only remember how I looked back then.</i>

481
00:41:14,935 --> 00:41:16,575
<i>Can you do that?</i>

482
00:41:16,575 --> 00:41:18,895
<i>Sunian,</i>

483
00:41:20,005 --> 00:41:22,925
<i>I won't be able to participate</i>

484
00:41:23,655 --> 00:41:27,955
<i>in your future.</i>

485
00:41:29,635 --> 00:41:32,675
<i>I'm so sorry that this has to happen.</i>

486
00:41:33,895 --> 00:41:38,115
<i>I want to see you go to college,</i>

487
00:41:38,115 --> 00:41:43,065
<i>get married, and have your own children.</i>

488
00:41:43,065 --> 00:41:48,095
<i>I'll definitely collude with your wife</i>

489
00:41:48,095 --> 00:41:53,305
<i>to play a prank on you and your father.</i>

490
00:41:53,305 --> 00:41:58,005
<i>You deserve that since you're such introverts.</i>

491
00:41:58,005 --> 00:42:02,285
<i>You never talk much to us girls.</i>

492
00:42:04,005 --> 00:42:06,155
<i>Sadly, I won't be able to hang around</i>

493
00:42:06,875 --> 00:42:09,595
<i>until that day comes.</i>

494
00:42:10,465 --> 00:42:16,655
<i>Therefore, I have one last thing to ask from you.</i>

495
00:42:17,355 --> 00:42:19,895
<i>Sunian,</i>

496
00:42:20,685 --> 00:42:26,945
<i>please cry as much as you want.</i>

497
00:42:26,945 --> 00:42:32,135
<i>Don't keep all the sorrow to yourself.</i>

498
00:42:32,135 --> 00:42:35,835
<i>I'm not that far away.</i>

499
00:42:35,835 --> 00:42:39,025
<i>I can still hear you.</i>

500
00:42:39,855 --> 00:42:42,705
<i>Cry as much as you want,</i>

501
00:42:42,705 --> 00:42:44,845
<i>okay?</i>

502
00:43:04,305 --> 00:43:08,185
<i>The greatest Ms. Jin Ning has passed away.</i>

503
00:43:09,605 --> 00:43:15,495
<i>Her departure left a big hole in our hearts.</i>

504
00:43:16,585 --> 00:43:21,695
<i>This house used to be a haven for me.</i>

505
00:43:21,695 --> 00:43:25,665
<i>Now, it's become a place</i>

506
00:43:25,665 --> 00:43:28,565
<i>that's filled with sighs and sorrow.</i>

